text:
Located in the industrial building of 163 Kally way.

Just happened to be here at this place for my breakfast. A very new place. Not sure about the lunch crowd. But breakfast here is stress free. Absolutely a bliss.

Think some stall hasn't open for business because it is too early.

The coffee/drinks  stall is run by Teo Chew City group.

Kopi C is thick and fragrant. $1.50

Many stalls here. (See photos)

Ordered from the economy rice stall fried beehoon with egg and prawn paste fried chicken. $4
Portion is reasonable. Food is tasty.

Leafin Plant-Based Vegan Food
Good portion, nutritious and delicious.

The fish soup is very nice! Ya should definitely try it.

The place is clean and well ventilated despite no air con.

Definitely worth a visit for lunch if you work nearby.

Lunch time very crowded on weekdays except fridays.
Food stalls not bad.
Coffee taste non consistent, some days ( or some person) have worse coffee.
Airy place but too little food choices.
